 63 this.ns = function(fn)
 64 {
 65     var ns = {};
 66     namespaces.push(fn, ns);
 67     return ns;

 69 
 70 this.initialize = function()
 71 {
 72     if (FBTrace.DBG_INITIALIZE)
 73         FBTrace.sysout("FBL.initialize BEGIN "+namespaces.length+" namespaces\n");
 74 
 75     for (var i = 0; i < namespaces.length; i += 2)
 76     {
 77         var fn = namespaces[i];
 78         var ns = namespaces[i+1];
 79         try
 80         {
 81             fn.apply(ns);
 82         }
 83         catch (exc)
 84         {
 85             if (exc.stack)
 86                 Components.utils.reportError("Firebug initialize FAILS "+exc+" "+exc.stack);
 87             else
 88                 Components.utils.reportError("Firebug initialize FAILS "+exc+" "+fn.toSource().substr(0,500));
 89         }
 90     }
 91 
 92     if (FBTrace.DBG_INITIALIZE)
 93         FBTrace.sysout("FBL.initialize END "+namespaces.length+" namespaces\n");
 94 };

 99 this.bind = function()  // fn, thisObject, args => thisObject.fn(arguments, args);
100 {
101    var args = cloneArray(arguments), fn = args.shift(), object = args.shift();
102    return function bind() { return fn.apply(object, arrayInsert(cloneArray(args), 0, arguments)); }
103 };
104 
105 this.bindFixed = function() // fn, thisObject, args => thisObject.fn(args);
106 {
107     var args = cloneArray(arguments), fn = args.shift(), object = args.shift();
108     return function() { return fn.apply(object, args); }
109 };

111 this.extend = function(l, r)
112 {
113     if (!l || !r)
114         throw new Error("FBL.extend on undefined object");
115 
116     var newOb = {};
117     for (var n in l)
118         newOb[n] = l[n];
119     for (var n in r)
120         newOb[n] = r[n];
121     return newOb;
122 };
123 
124 this.descend = function(prototypeParent, childProperties)
125 {
126     function protoSetter() {};
127     protoSetter.prototype = prototypeParent;
128     var newOb = new protoSetter();
129     for (var n in childProperties)
130         newOb[n] = childProperties[n];
131     return newOb;
132 };

137 this.keys = function(map)  // At least sometimes the keys will be on user-level window objects
138 {
139     var keys = [];
140     try
141     {
142         for (var name in map)  // enumeration is safe
143             keys.push(name);   // name is string, safe
144     }
145     catch (exc)
146     {
147         // Sometimes we get exceptions trying to iterate properties
148     }
149 
150     return keys;  // return is safe
151 };
152 
153 this.nonNumerickeys = function(map)  // At least sometimes the keys will be on user-level window objects
154 {
155     var keys = [];
156     try
157     {
158         for (var name in map)  // enumeration is safe
159         {
160             if (! (name instanceof number) )
161                 keys.push(name);   // name is string, safe
162         }
163     }
164     catch (exc)
165     {
166         // Sometimes we get exceptions trying to iterate properties
167     }
168 
169     return keys;  // return is safe
170 };

223 function cloneArray(array, fn)
224 {
225    var newArray = [];
226 
227    if (fn)
228        for (var i = 0; i < array.length; ++i)
229            newArray.push(fn(array[i]));
230    else
231        for (var i = 0; i < array.length; ++i)
232            newArray.push(array[i]);
233 
234    return newArray;
235 }

237 function extendArray(array, array2)
238 {
239    var newArray = [];
240    newArray.push.apply(newArray, array);
241    newArray.push.apply(newArray, array2);
242    return newArray;
243 }

248 function arrayInsert(array, index, other)
249 {
250    for (var i = 0; i < other.length; ++i)
251        array.splice(i+index, 0, other[i]);
252 
253    return array;
254 }

260 this.safeToString = function(ob)
261 {
262     try
263     {
264         if (!ob)
265         {
266             if (ob == undefined)
267                 return 'undefined';
268             if (ob == null)
269                 return 'null';
270             if (ob == false)
271                 return 'false';
272             return "";
273         }
274         if (ob && (typeof (ob['toString']) == "function") )
275             return ob.toString();
276         if (ob && typeof (ob['toSource']) == 'function')
277             return ob.toSource();
278        /* https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=522590 */
279         var str = "[";
280         for (var p in ob)
281             str += p+',';
282         return str + ']';
283 
284     }
285     catch (exc)
286     {
287         if (FBTrace.DBG_ERRORS)
288             FBTrace.sysout("safeToString FAILS "+exc, exc);
289     }
290     return "[unsupported: no toString() function in type "+typeof(ob)+"]";
291 };

322 this.convertToUnicode = function(text, charset)
323 {
324     if (!text)
325         return "";
326 
327     try
328     {
329         var conv = this.CCIN("@mozilla.org/intl/scriptableunicodeconverter",
330             "nsIScriptableUnicodeConverter");
331         conv.charset = charset ? charset : "UTF-8";
332         return conv.ConvertToUnicode(text);
333     }
334     catch (exc)
335     {
336         if (FBTrace.DBG_ERRORS)
337             FBTrace.sysout("lib.convertToUnicode: fails: for charset "+charset+" conv.charset:"+
338                 conv.charset+" exc: "+exc, exc);
339 
340         // the exception is worthless, make up a new one
341         throw new Error("Firebug failed to convert to unicode using charset: "+conv.charset+
342             " in @mozilla.org/intl/scriptableunicodeconverter");
343     }
344 };

387 this.createStyleSheet = function(doc, url)
388 {
389     var style = doc.createElementNS("http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml", "style");
390     style.setAttribute("charset","utf-8");
391     style.setAttribute("type", "text/css");
392 
393     var cssText = url ? this.getResource(url) : null;
394     if (cssText)
395     {
396         var index = url.lastIndexOf("/");
397         var absURL = url.substr(0, index+1);
398 
399         // Replace all relative URLs with absolute (using the passed url).
400         // Note that stylesheets can come from various extensions and the source can
401         // be even used in a browser env where relative URLs make more sense.
402         var expr = /url\(([\'"]?)(?![\'"]?(?:[a-z]+:|\/))/gi;
403         cssText = cssText.replace(expr, "url($1" + absURL);
404 
405         style.innerHTML = cssText;
406     }
407 
408     FBL.unwrapObject(style).firebugIgnore = true;
409     return style;
410 }
411

414     var heads = doc.getElementsByTagName("head");

416         heads[0].appendChild(style);
417     else

427 
428     var styleSheet = this.createStyleSheet(doc, uri);
429     styleSheet.setAttribute("id", uri);
430     this.addStyleSheet(doc, styleSheet);
431

475 /*
476  * $STR - intended for localization of a static string.
477  * $STRF - intended for localization of a string with dynamically inserted values.
478  * $STRP - intended for localization of a string with dynamically plural forms.
479  *
480  * Notes:
481  * 1) Name with _ in place of spaces is the key in the firebug.properties file.
482  * 2) If the specified key isn't localized for particular language, both methods use
483  *    the part after the last dot (in the specified name) as the return value.
484  *
485  * Examples:
486  * $STR("Label"); - search for key "Label" within the firebug.properties file
487  *                 and returns its value. If the key doesn't exist returns "Label".
488  *
489  * $STR("Button Label"); - search for key "Button_Label" withing the firebug.properties
490  *                        file. If the key doesn't exist returns "Button Label".
491  *
492  * $STR("net.Response Header"); - search for key "net.Response_Header". If the key doesn't
493  *                               exist returns "Response Header".
494  *
495  * firebug.properties:
496  * net.timing.Request_Time=Request Time: %S [%S]
497  *
498  * var param1 = 10;
499  * var param2 = "ms";
500  * $STRF("net.timing.Request Time", param1, param2);  -> "Request Time: 10 [ms]"
501  *
502  * - search for key "net.timing.Request_Time" within the firebug.properties file. Parameters
503  *   are inserted at specified places (%S) in the same order as they are passed. If the
504  *   key doesn't exist the method returns "Request Time".
505  */
506 function $STR(name, bundle)
507 {
508     var strKey = name.replace(' ', '_', "g");
509 
510     var useDefaultLocale = Firebug.getPref(Firebug.prefDomain, "useDefaultLocale");
511     if (!useDefaultLocale)
512     {
513         try
514         {
515             if (typeof bundle == "string")
516                 bundle = document.getElementById(bundle);
517 
518             if (bundle)
519                 return bundle.getString(strKey);
520             else
521                 return Firebug.getStringBundle().GetStringFromName(strKey);
522         }
523         catch (err)
524         {
525             if (FBTrace.DBG_LOCALE)
526                 FBTrace.sysout("lib.getString FAILS '" + name + "'", err);
527         }
528     }
529 
530     try
531     {
532         // The en-US string should be always available.
533         var bundle = Firebug.getDefaultStringBundle();
534         return bundle.GetStringFromName(strKey);
535     }
536     catch (err)
537     {
538         if (FBTrace.DBG_LOCALE)
539             FBTrace.sysout("lib.getString (default) FAILS '" + name + "'", err);
540     }
541 
542     // Don't panic now and use only the label after last dot.
543     var index = name.lastIndexOf(".");
544     if (index > 0 && name.charAt(index-1) != "\\")
545         name = name.substr(index + 1);
546     name = name.replace("_", " ", "g");
547     return name;
548 }
549 
550 function $STRF(name, args, bundle)
551 {
552     var strKey = name.replace(' ', '_', "g");
553 
554     var useDefaultLocale = Firebug.getPref(Firebug.prefDomain, "useDefaultLocale");
555     if (!useDefaultLocale)
556     {
557         try
558         {
559             // xxxHonza: Workaround for #485511
560             if (!bundle)
561                 bundle = "strings_firebug";
562 
563             if (typeof bundle == "string")
564                 bundle = document.getElementById(bundle);
565 
566             if (bundle)
567                 return bundle.getFormattedString(strKey, args);
568             else
569                 return Firebug.getStringBundle().formatStringFromName(strKey, args, args.length);
570         }
571         catch (err)
572         {
573             if (FBTrace.DBG_LOCALE)
574                 FBTrace.sysout("lib.getString FAILS '" + name + "'", err);
575         }
576     }
577 
578     try
579     {
580         // The en-US string should be always available.
581         var bundle = Firebug.getDefaultStringBundle();
582         return bundle.formatStringFromName(strKey, args, args.length);
583     }
584     catch (err)
585     {
586         if (FBTrace.DBG_LOCALE)
587             FBTrace.sysout("lib.getString (default) FAILS '" + name + "'", err);
588     }
589 
590     // Don't panic now and use only the label after last dot.
591     var index = name.lastIndexOf(".");
592     if (index > 0)
593         name = name.substr(index + 1);
594 
595     return name;
596 }
597 
598 function $STRP(name, args, index, bundle)
599 {
600     // xxxHonza:
601     // pluralRule from chrome://global/locale/intl.properties for Chinese is 1,
602     // which is wrong, it should be 0.
603 
604     var getPluralForm = PluralForm.get;
605     var getNumForms = PluralForm.numForms;
606 
607     // Get custom plural rule; otherwise the rule from chrome://global/locale/intl.properties
608     // (depends on the current locale) is used.
609     var pluralRule = Firebug.getPluralRule();
610     if (!isNaN(parseInt(pluralRule, 10)))
611         [getPluralForm, getNumForms] = PluralForm.makeGetter(pluralRule);
612 
613     // Index of the argument with plural form (there must be only one arg that needs plural form).
614     if (!index)
615         index = 0;
616 
617     // Get proper plural form from the string (depends on the current Firefox locale).
618     var translatedString = $STRF(name, args, bundle);
619     if (translatedString.search(";") > 0)
620         return getPluralForm(args[index], translatedString);
621 
622     // translatedString contains no ";", either rule 0 or getString fails
623     return translatedString;
624 }

630 /*
631  * Use the current value of the attribute as a key to look up the localized value.
632  */
633 this.internationalize = function(element, attr, args)
634 {
635     if (typeof element == "string")
636         element = document.getElementById(element);
637 
638     if (element)
639     {
640         var xulString = element.getAttribute(attr);
641         if (xulString)
642         {
643             var localized = args ? $STRF(xulString, args) : $STR(xulString);
644 
645             // Set localized value of the attribute.
646             element.setAttribute(attr, localized);
647         }
648     }
649     else
650     {
651         if (FBTrace.DBG_LOCALE)
652             FBTrace.sysout("Failed to internationalize element with attr "+attr+' args:'+args);
653     }
654 }
655 
656 this.internationalizeElements = function(doc, elements, attributes)
657 {
658     for (var i=0; i<elements.length; i++)
659     {
660         var element = doc.getElementById(elements[i]);
661         if (!element)
662             continue;
663 
664         for (var j=0; j<attributes.length; j++)
665         {
666             if (element.hasAttribute(attributes[j]))
667                 FBL.internationalize(element, attributes[j]);
668         }
669     }
670 }

675 this.isVisible = function(elt)
676 {
677     if (isElementXUL(elt))
678     {
679         //FBTrace.sysout("isVisible elt.offsetWidth: "+elt.offsetWidth+" offsetHeight:"+ elt.offsetHeight+" localName:"+ elt.localName+" nameSpace:"+elt.nameSpaceURI+"\n");
680         return (!elt.hidden && !elt.collapsed);
681     }
682 
683     try
684     {
685         return elt.offsetWidth > 0 ||
686             elt.offsetHeight > 0 ||
687             elt.localName in invisibleTags ||
688             isElementSVG(elt) ||
689             isElementMathML(elt);
690     }
691     catch (err)
692     {
693         if (FBTrace.DBG_ERRORS)
694             FBTrace.sysout("lib.isVisible; EXCEPTION " + err, err);
695     }
696 
697     return false;
698 };

736 this.ToggleBranch = function()
737 {
738     this.normal = {};
739     this.meta = {};
740 }
741 
742 this.metaNames =
743 [
744  'prototype',
745  'constructor',
746  '__proto__',
747  'toString',
748  'toSource',
749  'hasOwnProperty',
750  'getPrototypeOf',
751  '__defineGetter__',
752  '__defineSetter__',
753  '__lookupGetter__',
754  '__lookupSetter__',
755  '__noSuchMethod__',
756  'propertyIsEnumerable',
757  'isPrototypeOf',
758  'watch',
759  'unwatch',
760  'valueOf',
761  'toLocaleString'
762 ];
763 
764 this.ToggleBranch.prototype =
765 {
766     // Another implementation could simply prefix all keys with "#".
767     getMeta: function(name)
768     {
769         if (FBL.metaNames.indexOf(name) !== -1)
770             return "meta_"+name;
771     },
772 
773     get: function(name)  // return the toggle branch at name
774     {
775         var metaName = this.getMeta(name);
776         if (metaName)
777             var value = this.meta[metaName];
778         else if (this.normal.hasOwnProperty(name))
779             var value = this.normal[name];
780         else
781             var value = null;
782 
783         if (FBTrace.DBG_DOMPLATE)
784             if (value && !(value instanceof ToggleBranch)) FBTrace.sysout("ERROR ToggleBranch.get("+name+") not set to a ToggleBranch!");
785 
786         return value;
787     },
788 
789     set: function(name, value)  // value will be another toggle branch
790     {
791         if (FBTrace.DBG_DOMPLATE)
792             if (value && !(value instanceof ToggleBranch)) FBTrace.sysout("ERROR ToggleBranch.set("+name+","+value+") not set to a ToggleBranch!");
793 
794         var metaName = this.getMeta(name);
795         if (metaName)
796             return this.meta[metaName] = value;
797         else
798             return this.normal[name] = value;
799     },
800 
801     remove: function(name)  // remove the toggle branch at name
802     {
803         var metaName = this.getMeta(name);
804         if (metaName)
805             delete this.meta[metaName];
806         else
807             delete this.normal[name];
808     },
809 
810     toString: function()
811     {
812         return "[ToggleBranch]";
813     },
814 };

894 var classNameReCache={};
895 this.hasClass = function(node, name)
896 {
897     if (!node || node.nodeType != 1 || !node.className || name == '')
898         return false;
899 
900     if (name.indexOf(" ") != -1)
901     {
902         var classes = name.split(" "), len = classes.length, found=false;
903         for (var i = 0; i < len; i++)
904         {
905             var cls = classes[i].trim();
906             if (cls != "")
907             {
908                 if (this.hasClass(node, cls) == false)
909                     return false;
910                 found = true;
911             }
912         }
913         return found;
914     }
915 
916     var re;
917     if (name.indexOf("-") == -1)
918         re = classNameReCache[name] = classNameReCache[name] || new RegExp('(^|\\s)' + name + '(\\s|$)', "g");
919     else // XXXsroussey don't cache these, they are often setting values. Should be using setUserData/getUserData???
920         re = new RegExp('(^|\\s)' + name + '(\\s|$)', "g")
921     return node.className.search(re) != -1;
922 };
923 
924 this.setClass = function(node, name)
925 {
926     if (!node || node.nodeType != 1 || name == '')
927         return;
928 
929     if (name.indexOf(" ") != -1)
930     {
931         var classes = name.split(" "), len = classes.length;
932         for (var i = 0; i < len; i++)
933         {
934             var cls = classes[i].trim();
935             if (cls != "")
936             {
937                 this.setClass(node, cls);
938             }
939         }
940         return;
941     }
942     if (!this.hasClass(node, name))
943         node.className = node.className.trim() + " " + name;
944 };
945 
946 this.getClassValue = function(node, name)
947 {
948     var re = new RegExp(name+"-([^ ]+)");
949     var m = re.exec(node.className);
950     return m ? m[1] : "";
951 };
952 
953 this.removeClass = function(node, name)
954 {
955     if (!node || node.nodeType != 1 || node.className == '' || name == '')
956         return;
957 
958     if (name.indexOf(" ") != -1)
959     {
960         var classes = name.split(" "), len = classes.length;
961         for (var i = 0; i < len; i++)
962         {
963             var cls = classes[i].trim();
964             if (cls != "")
965             {
966                 if (this.hasClass(node, cls) == false)
967                     this.removeClass(node, cls);
968             }
969         }
970         return;
971     }
972 
973     var re;
974     if (name.indexOf("-") == -1)
975         re = classNameReCache[name] = classNameReCache[name] || new RegExp('(^|\\s)' + name + '(\\s|$)', "g");
976     else // XXXsroussey don't cache these, they are often setting values. Should be using setUserData/getUserData???
977         re = new RegExp('(^|\\s)' + name + '(\\s|$)', "g")
978 
979     node.className = node.className.replace(re, " ");
980 
981 };

1019         else

1193 this.findNext = function(node, criteria, upOnly, maxRoot)
1194 {
1195     if (!node)
1196         return null;
1197 
1198     if (!upOnly)
1199     {
1200         var next = this.findNextDown(node, criteria);
1201         if (next)
1202             return next;
1203     }
1204 
1205     for (var sib = node.nextSibling; sib; sib = sib.nextSibling)
1206     {
1207         if (criteria(sib))
1208             return sib;
1209 
1210         var next = this.findNextDown(sib, criteria);
1211         if (next)
1212             return next;
1213     }
1214 
1215     if (node.parentNode && node.parentNode != maxRoot)
1216         return this.findNext(node.parentNode, criteria, true, maxRoot);
1217 };
1218 
1219 this.findPrevious = function(node, criteria, downOnly, maxRoot)
1220 {
1221     if (!node)
1222         return null;
1223 
1224     for (var sib = node.previousSibling; sib; sib = sib.previousSibling)
1225     {
1226         var prev = this.findPreviousUp(sib, criteria);
1227         if (prev)
1228             return prev;
1229 
1230         if (criteria(sib))
1231             return sib;
1232     }
1233 
1234     if (!downOnly)
1235     {
1236         var next = this.findPreviousUp(node, criteria);
1237         if (next)
1238             return next;
1239     }
1240 
1241     if (node.parentNode && node.parentNode != maxRoot)
1242     {
1243         if (criteria(node.parentNode))
1244             return node.parentNode;
1245 
1246         return this.findPrevious(node.parentNode, criteria, true);
1247     }
1248 };

1296 this.XW_instanceof = function(obj, type) // Cross Window instanceof; type is local to this window
1297 {
1298     if (obj instanceof type)
1299         return true;  // within-window test
1300 
1301     if (!type)
1302         return false;
1303     if (!obj)
1304         return (type == "undefined");
1305 
1306     // compare strings: obj constructor.name to type.name.
1307     // This is not perfect, we should compare type.prototype to object.__proto__, but mostly code does not change the constructor object.
1308     do
1309     {
1310         if (obj.constructor && obj.constructor.name == type.name)  // then the function that constructed us is the argument
1311             return true;
1312     }
1313     while(obj = obj.__proto__);  // walk the prototype chain.
1314     return false;
1315     // https://developer.mozilla.org/en/Core_JavaScript_1.5_Guide/Property_Inheritance_Revisited/Determining_Instance_Relationships
1316 }

1369 /**
1370  * Gets an XPath for an element which describes its hierarchical location.
1371  */
1372 this.getElementXPath = function(element)
1373 {
1374     if (element && element.id)
1375         return '//*[@id="' + element.id + '"]';
1376     else
1377         return this.getElementTreeXPath(element);

1380 this.getElementTreeXPath = function(element)
1381 {
1382     var paths = [];
1383 
1384     // Use nodeName (instead of localName) so namespace prefix is included (if any).
1385     for (; element && element.nodeType == 1; element = element.parentNode)
1386     {
1387         var index = 0;
1388         for (var sibling = element.previousSibling; sibling; sibling = sibling.previousSibling)
1389         {
1390             // Ignore document type declaration.
1391             if (sibling.nodeType == Node.DOCUMENT_TYPE_NODE)
1392                 continue;
1393 
1394             if (sibling.nodeName == element.nodeName)
1395                 ++index;
1396         }
1397 
1398         var tagName = element.nodeName.toLowerCase();
1399         var pathIndex = (index ? "[" + (index+1) + "]" : "");
1400         paths.splice(0, 0, tagName + pathIndex);
1401     }
1402 
1403     return paths.length ? "/" + paths.join("/") : null;
1404 };

1411     {
1412         var selector = this.getElementCSSSelector(element);
1413         paths.splice(0, 0, selector);
1414     }
1415 
1416     return paths.length ? paths.join(" ") : null;
1417 };

1419 this.cssToXPath = function(rule)
1420 {
1421     var regElement = /^([#.]?)([a-z0-9\\*_-]*)((\|)([a-z0-9\\*_-]*))?/i;
1422     var regAttr1 = /^\[([^\]]*)\]/i;
1423     var regAttr2 = /^\[\s*([^~=\s]+)\s*(~?=)\s*"([^"]+)"\s*\]/i;
1424     var regPseudo = /^:([a-z_-])+/i;
1425     var regCombinator = /^(\s*[>+\s])?/i;
1426     var regComma = /^\s*,/i;
1427 
1428     var index = 1;
1429     var parts = ["//", "*"];
1430     var lastRule = null;
1431 
1432     while (rule.length && rule != lastRule)
1433     {
1434         lastRule = rule;
1435 
1436         // Trim leading whitespace
1437         rule = this.trim(rule);
1438         if (!rule.length)
1439             break;
1440 
1441         // Match the element identifier
1442         var m = regElement.exec(rule);
1443         if (m)
1444         {
1445             if (!m[1])
1446             {
1447                 // XXXjoe Namespace ignored for now
1448                 if (m[5])
1449                     parts[index] = m[5];
1450                 else
1451                     parts[index] = m[2];
1452             }
1453             else if (m[1] == '#')
1454                 parts.push("[@id='" + m[2] + "']");
1455             else if (m[1] == '.')
1456                 parts.push("[contains(concat(' ',normalize-space(@class),' '), ' " + m[2] + " ')]");
1457 
1458             rule = rule.substr(m[0].length);
1459         }
1460 
1461         // Match attribute selectors
1462         m = regAttr2.exec(rule);
1463         if (m)
1464         {
1465             if (m[2] == "~=")
1466                 parts.push("[contains(@" + m[1] + ", '" + m[3] + "')]");
1467             else
1468                 parts.push("[@" + m[1] + "='" + m[3] + "']");
1469 
1470             rule = rule.substr(m[0].length);
1471         }
1472         else
1473         {
1474             m = regAttr1.exec(rule);
1475             if (m)
1476             {
1477                 parts.push("[@" + m[1] + "]");
1478                 rule = rule.substr(m[0].length);
1479             }
1480         }
1481 
1482         // Skip over pseudo-classes and pseudo-elements, which are of no use to us
1483         m = regPseudo.exec(rule);
1484         while (m)
1485         {
1486             rule = rule.substr(m[0].length);
1487             m = regPseudo.exec(rule);
1488         }
1489 
1490         // Match combinators
1491         m = regCombinator.exec(rule);
1492         if (m && m[0].length)
1493         {
1494             if (m[0].indexOf(">") != -1)
1495                 parts.push("/");
1496             else if (m[0].indexOf("+") != -1)
1497                 parts.push("/following-sibling::");
1498             else
1499                 parts.push("//");
1500 
1501             index = parts.length;
1502             parts.push("*");
1503             rule = rule.substr(m[0].length);
1504         }
1505 
1506         m = regComma.exec(rule);
1507         if (m)
1508         {
1509             parts.push(" | ", "//", "*");
1510             index = parts.length-1;
1511             rule = rule.substr(m[0].length);
1512         }
1513     }
1514 
1515     var xpath = parts.join("");
1516     return xpath;
1517 };

1525 this.getElementsByXPath = function(doc, xpath)
1526 {
1527     var nodes = [];
1528 
1529     try {
1530         var result = doc.evaluate(xpath, doc, null, XPathResult.ANY_TYPE, null);
1531         for (var item = result.iterateNext(); item; item = result.iterateNext())
1532             nodes.push(item);
1533     }
1534     catch (exc)
1535     {
1536         // Invalid xpath expressions make their way here sometimes.  If that happens,
1537         // we still want to return an empty set without an exception.
1538     }
1539 
1540     return nodes;
1541 };
1542 
1543 this.getRuleMatchingElements = function(rule, doc)

1562 this.getClientOffset = function(elt)
1563 {

1565     {
1566         var p = elt.offsetParent;
1567 
1568         var style = view.getComputedStyle(elt, "");

1571             coords.x += elt.offsetLeft + parseInt(style.borderLeftWidth);

1574

1578                 addOffset(p, coords, view);

1586     {

1588         addOffset(elt, coords, view);

1671 this.linesIntoCenterView = function(element, scrollBox)  // {before: int, after: int}
1672 {
1673     if (!scrollBox)
1674         scrollBox = this.getOverflowParent(element);
1675

1680

1682     var bottomSpace = (scrollBox.scrollTop + scrollBox.clientHeight)
1683             - (offset.y + element.offsetHeight);
1684

1686     {
1687         var split = (scrollBox.clientHeight/2);
1688         var centerY = offset.y - split;
1689         scrollBox.scrollTop = centerY;
1690         topSpace = split;
1691         bottomSpace = split -  element.offsetHeight;
1692     }
1693 
1694     return {before: Math.round((topSpace/element.offsetHeight) + 0.5),
1695             after: Math.round((bottomSpace/element.offsetHeight) + 0.5) }
1696 };

2025 this.getElementHTML = function(element)
2026 {
2027     var self=this;
2028     function toHTML(elt)
2029     {
2030         if (elt.nodeType == Node.ELEMENT_NODE)
2031         {
2032             if (unwrapObject(elt).firebugIgnore)
2033                 return;
2034 
2035             var nodeName = getNodeName(elt);
2036             html.push('<', nodeName);
2037 
2038             for (var i = 0; i < elt.attributes.length; ++i)
2039             {
2040                 var attr = elt.attributes[i];
2041 
2042                 // Hide attributes set by Firebug
2043                 if (attr.localName.indexOf("firebug-") == 0)
2044                     continue;
2045 
2046                 // MathML
2047                 if (attr.localName.indexOf("-moz-math") == 0)
2048                 {
2049                     // just hide for now
2050                     continue;
2051                 }
2052 
2053                 html.push(' ', attr.nodeName, '="', escapeForElementAttribute(attr.nodeValue),'"');
2054             }
2055 
2056             if (elt.firstChild)
2057             {
2058                 html.push('>');
2059 
2060                 var pureText=true;
2061                 for (var child = element.firstChild; child; child = child.nextSibling)
2062                     pureText=pureText && (child.nodeType == Node.TEXT_NODE);
2063 
2064                 if (pureText)
2065                     html.push(escapeForHtmlEditor(elt.textContent));
2066                 else {
2067                     for (var child = elt.firstChild; child; child = child.nextSibling)
2068                         toHTML(child);
2069                 }
2070 
2071                 html.push('</', nodeName, '>');
2072             }
2073             else if (isElementSVG(elt) || isElementMathML(elt))
2074             {
2075                 html.push('/>');
2076             }
2077             else if (self.isSelfClosing(elt))
2078             {
2079                 html.push((isElementXHTML(elt))?'/>':'>');
2080             }
2081             else
2082             {
2083                 html.push('></', nodeName, '>');
2084             }
2085         }
2086         else if (elt.nodeType == Node.TEXT_NODE)
2087             html.push(escapeForTextNode(elt.textContent));
2088         else if (elt.nodeType == Node.CDATA_SECTION_NODE)
2089             html.push('<![CDATA[', elt.nodeValue, ']]>');
2090         else if (elt.nodeType == Node.COMMENT_NODE)
2091             html.push('<!--', elt.nodeValue, '-->');
2092     }
2093 
2094     var html = [];
2095     toHTML(element);
2096     return html.join("");
2097 };

2221 function addEntityMapToList(ccode, entity)
2222 {

2269 //************************************************************************************************
2270 // Entity escaping
2271 
2272 var entityConversionRegexes = {
2273         normal : {},
2274         reverse : {}
2275     };
2276 
2277 var escapeEntitiesRegEx = {
2278     normal : function(list)
2279     {
2280         var chars = [];
2281         for ( var ch in list)
2282         {
2283             chars.push(ch);
2284         }
2285         return new RegExp('([' + chars.join('') + '])', 'gm');
2286     },
2287     reverse : function(list)
2288     {
2289         var chars = [];
2290         for ( var ch in list)
2291         {
2292             chars.push(ch);
2293         }
2294         return new RegExp('(' + chars.join('|') + ')', 'gm');
2295     }
2296 };
2297 
2298 function getEscapeRegexp(direction, lists)
2299 {
2300     var name = '', re;
2301     var groups = [].concat(lists);
2302     for (i = 0; i < groups.length; i++)
2303     {
2304         name += groups[i].group;
2305     }
2306     re = entityConversionRegexes[direction][name];
2307     if (!re)
2308     {
2309         var list = {};
2310         if (groups.length > 1)
2311         {
2312             for ( var i = 0; i < groups.length; i++)
2313             {
2314                 var aList = entityConversionLists[direction][groups[i].group];
2315                 for ( var item in aList)
2316                     list[item] = aList[item];
2317             }
2318         } else if (groups.length==1)
2319         {
2320             list = entityConversionLists[direction][groups[0].group]; // faster for special case
2321         } else {
2322             list = {}; // perhaps should print out an error here?
2323         }
2324         re = entityConversionRegexes[direction][name] = escapeEntitiesRegEx[direction](list);
2325     }
2326     return re;
2327 }
2328 
2329 function createSimpleEscape(name, direction)
2330 {
2331     return function(value)
2332     {
2333         var list = entityConversionLists[direction][name];
2334         return String(value).replace(
2335                 getEscapeRegexp(direction, {
2336                     group : name,
2337                     list : list
2338                 }),
2339                 function(ch)
2340                 {
2341                     return list[ch];
2342                 }
2343                );
2344     }
2345 }

2347 function escapeGroupsForEntities(str, lists)
2348 {
2349     lists = [].concat(lists);
2350     var re = getEscapeRegexp('normal', lists),
2351         split = String(str).split(re),
2352         len = split.length,
2353         results = [],
2354         cur, r, i, ri = 0, l, list, last = '';
2355     if (!len)
2356         return [ {
2357             str : String(str),
2358             group : '',
2359             name : ''
2360         } ];
2361     for (i = 0; i < len; i++)
2362     {
2363         cur = split[i];
2364         if (cur == '')
2365             continue;
2366         for (l = 0; l < lists.length; l++)
2367         {
2368             list = lists[l];
2369             r = entityConversionLists.normal[list.group][cur];
2370             // if (cur == ' ' && list.group == 'whitespace' && last == ' ') // only show for runs of more than one space
2371             //     r = ' ';
2372             if (r)
2373             {
2374                 results[ri] = {
2375                     'str' : r,
2376                     'class' : list['class'],
2377                     'extra' : list.extra[cur] ? list['class']
2378                             + list.extra[cur] : ''
2379                 };
2380                 break;
2381             }
2382         }
2383         // last=cur;
2384         if (!r)
2385             results[ri] = {
2386                 'str' : cur,
2387                 'class' : '',
2388                 'extra' : ''
2389             };
2390         ri++;
2391     }
2392     return results;
2393 }

2398 function unescapeEntities(str, lists)
2399 {
2400     var re = getEscapeRegexp('reverse', lists),
2401         split = String(str).split(re),
2402         len = split.length,
2403         results = [],
2404         cur, r, i, ri = 0, l, list;
2405     if (!len)
2406         return str;
2407     lists = [].concat(lists);
2408     for (i = 0; i < len; i++)
2409     {
2410         cur = split[i];
2411         if (cur == '')
2412             continue;
2413         for (l = 0; l < lists.length; l++)
2414         {
2415             list = lists[l];
2416             r = entityConversionLists.reverse[list.group][cur];
2417             if (r)
2418             {
2419                 results[ri] = r;
2420                 break;
2421             }
2422         }
2423         if (!r)
2424             results[ri] = cur;
2425         ri++;
2426     }
2427     return results.join('') || '';
2428 }

2475 this.cropString = function(text, limit, alterText)
2476 {
2477     if (!alterText)
2478         alterText = "...";
2479 
2480     // Make sure it's a string.
2481     text = text + "";
2482 
2483     // Use default limit if necessary.
2484     if (!limit)
2485         limit = Firebug.stringCropLength;
2486 
2487     // Crop the string only if a limit is actualy specified.
2488     if (limit <= 0)
2489         return text;
2490 
2491     var halfLimit = (limit / 2);
2492     halfLimit -= 2; // adjustment for alterText's increase in size
2493 
2494     if (text.length > limit)
2495         return text.substr(0, halfLimit) + alterText + text.substr(text.length-halfLimit);
2496 
2497     return text;
2498 };

2557 this.wrapText = function(text, noEscapeHTML)
2558 {
2559     var reNonAlphaNumeric = /[^A-Za-z_$0-9'"-]/;
2560 
2561     var html = [];
2562     var wrapWidth = Firebug.textWrapWidth;
2563 
2564     // Split long text into lines and put every line into a <code> element (only in case
2565     // if noEscapeHTML is false). This is useful for automatic scrolling when searching
2566     // within response body (in order to scroll we need an element).
2567     // Don't use <pre> elements since this adds additional new line endings when copying
2568     // selected source code using Firefox->Edit->Copy (Ctrl+C) (issue 2093).
2569     var lines = this.splitLines(text);
2570     for (var i = 0; i < lines.length; ++i)
2571     {
2572         var line = lines[i];
2573 
2574         if (wrapWidth > 0)
2575         {
2576             while (line.length > wrapWidth)
2577             {
2578                 var m = reNonAlphaNumeric.exec(line.substr(wrapWidth, 100));
2579                 var wrapIndex = wrapWidth + (m ? m.index : 0);
2580                 var subLine = line.substr(0, wrapIndex);
2581                 line = line.substr(wrapIndex);
2582 
2583                 if (!noEscapeHTML) html.push("<code class=\"wrappedText focusRow\" role=\"listitem\">");
2584                 html.push(noEscapeHTML ? subLine : escapeForTextNode(subLine));
2585                 if (!noEscapeHTML) html.push("</code>");
2586             }
2587         }
2588 
2589         if (!noEscapeHTML) html.push("<code class=\"wrappedText focusRow\" role=\"listitem\">");
2590         html.push(noEscapeHTML ? line : escapeForTextNode(line));
2591         if (!noEscapeHTML) html.push("</code>");
2592     }
2593 
2594     return html;
2595 }

2597 this.insertWrappedText = function(text, textBox, noEscapeHTML)
2598 {
2599     var html = this.wrapText(text, noEscapeHTML);
2600     textBox.innerHTML = "<pre role=\"list\">" + html.join("") + "</pre>";
2601 }

2614 this.cleanIndentation = function(text)
2615 {
2616     var lines = this.splitLines(text);
2617 
2618     var minIndent = -1;
2619     for (var i = 0; i < lines.length; ++i)
2620     {
2621         var line = lines[i];
2622         var indent = getIndent(line);
2623         if (minIndent == -1 && line && !this.isWhitespace(line))
2624             minIndent = indent;
2625         if (indent >= minIndent)
2626             lines[i] = line.substr(minIndent);
2627     }
2628     return lines.join("");

2787 /*
2788  * Converts a Mozilla stack frame to a frameXB
2789  */
2790 this.getCorrectedStackTrace = function(frame, context)
2791 {
2792     try
2793     {
2794         var trace = new this.StackTrace();
2795         var newestFrame = null;
2796         var nextOlderFrame = null;
2797         for (; frame && frame.isValid; frame = frame.callingFrame)
2798         {
2799             if (!(Firebug.filterSystemURLs && this.isSystemURL(FBL.normalizeURL(frame.script.fileName))))
2800             {
2801                 var stackFrame = this.getStackFrame(frame, context, newestFrame);
2802                 if (stackFrame)
2803                 {
2804                     if (!newestFrame)
2805                         newestFrame = stackFrame;
2806 
2807                     if (context.currentFrame && context.currentFrame === frame)
2808                         trace.currentFrameIndex = trace.length;
2809 
2810                     stackFrame.setCallingFrame(nextOlderFrame, trace.frames.length);
2811                     nextOlderFrame = stackFrame;
2812                     trace.frames.push(stackFrame);
2813                 }
2814             }
2815             else
2816             {
2817                 if (FBTrace.DBG_STACK)
2818                     FBTrace.sysout("lib.getCorrectedStackTrace isSystemURL frame.script.fileName "+frame.script.fileName+"\n");
2819             }
2820         }
2821 
2822         if (trace.frames.length > 100)  // TODO in the loop above
2823         {
2824             var originalLength = trace.frames.length;
2825             trace.frames.splice(50, originalLength - 100);
2826             var excuse = "(eliding "+(originalLength - 100)+" frames)";
2827             trace.frames[50] = new this.StackFrame({href: excuse}, 0, excuse, [], null, null, context);
2828         }
2829 
2830     }
2831     catch (exc)
2832     {
2833         if (FBTrace.DBG_ERRORS)
2834             FBTrace.sysout("getCorrectedStackTrace FAILS "+exc, exc);
2835     }
2836     return trace;
2837 };

2839 /*
2840  * Converts from Mozilla stack frame to frameXB
2841  */
2842 
2843 this.getStackFrame = function(frame, context, newestFrameXB)
2844 {
2845     if (frame.isNative || frame.isDebugger)
2846     {
2847         var excuse = (frame.isNative) ?  "(native)" : "(debugger)";
2848         if (FBTrace.DBG_STACK) FBTrace.sysout("lib.getStackFrame "+excuse+" frame\n");
2849         return new this.StackFrame({href: excuse}, 0, excuse, [], null, null, context, newestFrameXB);
2850     }
2851     try
2852     {
2853         var sourceFile = Firebug.SourceFile.getSourceFileByScript(context, frame.script);
2854         if (sourceFile)
2855         {
2856             var url = sourceFile.href;
2857             var analyzer = sourceFile.getScriptAnalyzer(frame.script);
2858 
2859             var lineNo = analyzer.getSourceLineFromFrame(context, frame);
2860             var fncSpec = analyzer.getFunctionDescription(frame.script, context, frame);
2861             if (!fncSpec.name || fncSpec.name === "anonymous")
2862             {
2863                 fncSpec.name =  this.guessFunctionName(url, frame.script.baseLineNumber, context);
2864                 if (!fncSpec.name)
2865                     fncSpec.name = "?";
2866             }
2867 
2868             if (FBTrace.DBG_STACK) FBTrace.sysout("lib.getStackFrame "+fncSpec.name, {sourceFile: sourceFile, script: frame.script, fncSpec: fncSpec, analyzer: analyzer});
2869             return new this.StackFrame(sourceFile, lineNo, fncSpec.name, fncSpec.args, frame, null, sourceFile.context, newestFrameXB);
2870         }
2871         else
2872         {
2873             if (FBTrace.DBG_STACK)
2874                 FBTrace.sysout("lib.getStackFrame NO sourceFile tag@file:"+frame.script.tag+"@"+frame.script.fileName, frame.script.functionSource);
2875 
2876             var script = frame.script;
2877 
2878             return new this.StackFrame({href: FBL.normalizeURL(script.fileName)}, frame.line, script.functionName, [], frame, null, context, newestFrameXB);
2879         }
2880     }
2881     catch (exc)
2882     {
2883         if (FBTrace.DBG_STACK) FBTrace.sysout("getCorrectedStackTrace fails: "+exc, exc);
2884         return null;
2885     }
2886 };

3033                          })();

3040                      scopeVars = {error: "Mozilla error: invalid scope variables"};
3041                  }

3749 this.getExpressionAt = function(text, charOffset)
3750 {
3751     var offset = 0;
3752     for (var m = reWord.exec(text); m; m = reWord.exec(text.substr(offset)))
3753     {
3754         var word = m[0];
3755         var wordOffset = offset+m.index;
3756         if (charOffset >= wordOffset && charOffset <= wordOffset+word.length)
3757         {
3758             var innerOffset = charOffset-wordOffset;
3759             var dots = word.substr(0, innerOffset).split(".").length;
3760             var subExpr = word.split(".").slice(0, dots).join(".");
3761             return {expr: subExpr, offset: wordOffset};
3762         }
3763 
3764         offset = wordOffset+word.length;
3765     }
3766 
3767     return {expr: null, offset: -1};
3768 };

3877 this.dispatch = function(listeners, name, args)
3878 {
3879     if (!listeners)
3880         return;
3881 
3882     try {
3883         if (FBTrace.DBG_DISPATCH)
3884             var noMethods = [];
3885 
3886         for (var i = 0; i < listeners.length; ++i)
3887         {
3888             var listener = listeners[i];
3889             if (!listener)
3890             {
3891                 if (FBTrace.DBG_DISPATCH || FBTrace.DBG_ERRORS)
3892                     FBTrace.sysout("FBL.dispatch ERROR "+i+" "+name+" to null listener.");
3893                 continue;
3894             }
3895             if ( listener[name] )
3896             {
3897                 //FBTrace.sysout("FBL.dispatch "+i+") "+name+" to "+listener.dispatchName);
3898                 try
3899                 {
3900                     listener[name].apply(listener, args);
3901                 }
3902                 catch(exc)
3903                 {
3904                     if (FBTrace.DBG_ERRORS)
3905                     {
3906                         if (exc.stack)
3907                         {
3908                             var stack = exc.stack;
3909                             exc.stack = stack.split('\n');
3910                         }
3911                         var culprit = listeners[i] ? listeners[i].dispatchName : null;
3912                         FBTrace.sysout(" Exception in lib.dispatch "+(culprit?culprit+".":"")+ name+": "+exc+" in "+(exc.fileName?exc.fileName:"")+(exc.lineNumber?":"+exc.lineNumber:""), exc);
3913                     }
3914                 }
3915             }
3916             else
3917             {
3918                 if (FBTrace.DBG_DISPATCH)
3919                 {
3920                     //FBTrace.sysout("FBL.dispatch noMethod in "+i+"/"+listeners.length+") "+name+" to "+listener.dispatchName);
3921                     noMethods.push(listener);
3922                 }
3923             }
3924         }
3925         if (FBTrace.DBG_DISPATCH)
3926             FBTrace.sysout("FBL.dispatch "+name+" to "+listeners.length+" listeners, "+noMethods.length+" had no such method:", noMethods);
3927     }
3928     catch (exc)
3929     {
3930         if (FBTrace.DBG_ERRORS)
3931         {
3932             if (exc.stack)
3933             {
3934                 var stack = exc.stack;
3935                 exc.stack = stack.split('\n');
3936             }
3937             var culprit = listeners[i] ? listeners[i].dispatchName : null;
3938             FBTrace.sysout(" Exception in lib.dispatch "+(culprit?culprit+".":"")+ name+": "+exc, exc);
3939             window.dump(FBL.getStackDump());
3940         }
3941     }
3942 };

3944 this.dispatch2 = function(listeners, name, args)
3945 {
3946     try
3947     {
3948         if (FBTrace.DBG_DISPATCH)
3949             var noMethods = [];
3950 
3951         for (var i = 0; i < listeners.length; ++i)
3952         {
3953             var listener = listeners[i];
3954             if ( listener.hasOwnProperty(name) )
3955             {
3956                 var result = listener[name].apply(listener, args);
3957                 if ( result )
3958                 {
3959                     if (FBTrace.DBG_DISPATCH)
3960                         FBTrace.sysout("dispatch2 "+name+" to "+listeners.length+" listeners, result "+result, result);
3961                     return result;
3962                 }
3963             }
3964             else
3965             {
3966                 if (FBTrace.DBG_DISPATCH)
3967                     noMethods.push(listener);
3968             }
3969         }
3970         if (FBTrace.DBG_DISPATCH)
3971             FBTrace.sysout("FBL.dispatch2 "+name+" to "+listeners.length+" listeners, "+noMethods.length+" had no such method:", noMethods);
3972     }
3973     catch (exc)
3974     {
3975         if (FBTrace.DBG_ERRORS)
3976         {
3977             if (exc.stack) exc.stack = exc.stack.split('/n');
3978             FBTrace.sysout(" Exception in lib.dispatch2 "+ name+" exc:"+exc, exc);
3979         }
3980     }

4129 this.splitDataURL = function(url)
4130 {
4131     var mark = url.indexOf('data:');
4132     if (mark != 0)
4133         return false; //  the first 5 chars must be 'data:'
4134 
4135     var point = url.indexOf(',', 5);
4136     if (point < 5)
4137         return false; // syntax error
4138 
4139     var props = { encodedContent: url.substr(point+1) };
4140 
4141     var metadataBuffer = url.substring(5, point);
4142     var metadata = metadataBuffer.split(';');
4143     for (var i = 0; i < metadata.length; i++)
4144     {
4145         var nv = metadata[i].split('=');
4146         if (nv.length == 2)
4147             props[nv[0]] = nv[1];
4148     }
4149 
4150     // Additional Firebug-specific properties
4151     if (props.hasOwnProperty('fileName'))
4152     {
4153          var caller_URL = decodeURIComponent(props['fileName']);
4154          var caller_split = this.splitURLTrue(caller_URL);
4155 
4156          props['fileName'] = caller_URL;
4157 
4158         if (props.hasOwnProperty('baseLineNumber'))  // this means it's probably an eval()
4159         {
4160             props['path'] = caller_split.path;
4161             props['line'] = props['baseLineNumber'];
4162             var hint = decodeURIComponent(props['encodedContent']).substr(0,200).replace(/\s*$/, "");
4163             props['name'] =  'eval->'+hint;
4164         }
4165         else
4166         {
4167             props['name'] = caller_split.name;
4168             props['path'] = caller_split.path;
4169         }
4170     }
4171     else
4172     {
4173         if (!props.hasOwnProperty('path'))
4174             props['path'] = "data:";
4175         if (!props.hasOwnProperty('name'))
4176             props['name'] =  decodeURIComponent(props['encodedContent']).substr(0,200).replace(/\s*$/, "");
4177     }
4178 
4179     return props;
4180 };

4389 this.absoluteURLWithDots = function(url, baseURL)
4390 {
4391     // Should implement http://www.apps.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3986.html#sec-5
4392     // or use the newURI approach described in issue 3110.
4393     // See tests/content/lib/absoluteURLs.js
4394 
4395     if (url.length === 0)
4396         return baseURL;
4397 
4398     var R_query_index = url.indexOf('?');
4399     var R_head = url;
4400     if (R_query_index !== -1)
4401         R_head = url.substr(0, R_query_index);
4402 
4403     if (url.indexOf(':') !== -1)
4404         return url;
4405 
4406     var reURL = /(([^:]+:)\/{1,2}[^\/]*)(.*?)$/;
4407     var m_url = reURL.exec(R_head);
4408     if (m_url)
4409         return url;
4410 
4411     var B_query_index = baseURL.indexOf('?');
4412     var B_head = baseURL;
4413     if (B_query_index !== -1)
4414         B_head = baseURL.substr(0, B_query_index);
4415 
4416     if (url[0] === "?")   // cases where R.path is empty.
4417         return B_head + url;
4418     if  (url[0] === "#")
4419         return baseURL.split('#')[0]+url;
4420 
4421     var m = reURL.exec(B_head);
4422     if (!m)
4423         return "";
4424 
4425     var head = m[1];
4426     var tail = m[3];
4427     if (url.substr(0, 2) == "//")
4428         return m[2] + url;
4429     else if (url[0] == "/")
4430     {
4431         return head + url;
4432     }
4433     else if (tail[tail.length-1] == "/")
4434         return baseURL + url;
4435     else
4436     {
4437         var parts = tail.split("/");
4438         return head + parts.slice(0, parts.length-1).join("/") + "/" + url;
4439     }
4440 }

4442 this.normalizeURL = function(url)  // this gets called a lot, any performance improvement welcome
4443 {
4444     if (!url)
4445         return "";
4446     // Replace one or more characters that are not forward-slash followed by /.., by space.
4447     if (url.length < 255) // guard against monsters.
4448     {
4449         // Replace one or more characters that are not forward-slash followed by /.., by space.
4450         url = url.replace(/[^/]+\/\.\.\//, "", "g");
4451         // Issue 1496, avoid #
4452         url = url.replace(/#.*/,"");
4453         // For some reason, JSDS reports file URLs like "file:/" instead of "file:///", so they
4454         // don't match up with the URLs we get back from the DOM
4455         url = url.replace(/file:\/([^/])/g, "file:///$1");
4456         // For script tags inserted dynamically sometimes the script.fileName is bogus
4457         url = url.replace(/[^\s]*\s->\s/, "");
4458 
4459         if (url.indexOf('chrome:')==0)
4460         {
4461             var m = reChromeCase.exec(url);  // 1 is package name, 2 is path
4462             if (m)
4463             {
4464                 url = "chrome://"+m[1].toLowerCase()+"/"+m[2];
4465             }
4466         }
4467     }
4468     return url;
4469 };
4470 
4471 this.denormalizeURL = function(url)
4472 {
4473     return url.replace(/file:\/\/\//g, "file:/");
4474 };

4476 this.parseURLParams = function(url)
4477 {
4478     var q = url ? url.indexOf("?") : -1;
4479     if (q == -1)
4480         return [];
4481 
4482     var search = url.substr(q+1);
4483     var h = search.lastIndexOf("#");
4484     if (h != -1)
4485         search = search.substr(0, h);
4486 
4487     if (!search)
4488         return [];
4489 
4490     return this.parseURLEncodedText(search);

4493 this.parseURLEncodedText = function(text, noLimit)
4494 {
4495     const maxValueLength = 25000;
4496 
4497     var params = [];
4498 
4499     // In case the text is empty just return the empty parameters
4500     if(text == '')
4501       return params;
4502 
4503     // Unescape '+' characters that are used to encode a space.
4504     // See section 2.2.in RFC 3986: http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3986.txt
4505     text = text.replace(/\+/g, " ");
4506 
4507     // Unescape '&' character
4508     text = this.unescapeForURL(text);
4509 
4510     function decodeText(text)
4511     {
4512         try
4513         {
4514             return decodeURIComponent(text);
4515         }
4516         catch (e)
4517         {
4518             return decodeURIComponent(unescape(text));
4519         }
4520     }
4521 
4522     var args = text.split("&");
4523     for (var i = 0; i < args.length; ++i)
4524     {
4525         try
4526         {
4527             var index = args[i].indexOf("=");
4528             if (index != -1)
4529             {
4530                 var paramName = args[i].substring(0, index);
4531                 var paramValue = args[i].substring(index + 1);
4532 
4533                 if (paramValue.length > maxValueLength && !noLimit)
4534                     paramValue = this.$STR("LargeData");
4535 
4536                 params.push({name: decodeText(paramName), value: decodeText(paramValue)});
4537             }
4538             else
4539             {
4540                 var paramName = args[i];
4541                 params.push({name: decodeText(paramName), value: ""});
4542             }
4543         }
4544         catch (e)
4545         {
4546             if (FBTrace.DBG_ERRORS)
4547             {
4548                 FBTrace.sysout("parseURLEncodedText EXCEPTION ", e);
4549                 FBTrace.sysout("parseURLEncodedText EXCEPTION URI", args[i]);
4550             }
4551         }
4552     }
4553 
4554     params.sort(function(a, b) { return a.name <= b.name ? -1 : 1; });
4555 
4556     return params;
4557 };

4559 this.reEncodeURL = function(file, text, noLimit)
4560 {
4561     var lines = text.split("\n");
4562     var params = this.parseURLEncodedText(lines[lines.length-1], noLimit);
4563 
4564     var args = [];
4565     for (var i = 0; i < params.length; ++i)
4566         args.push(encodeURIComponent(params[i].name)+"="+encodeURIComponent(params[i].value));
4567 
4568     var url = file.href;
4569     url += (url.indexOf("?") == -1 ? "?" : "&") + args.join("&");
4570 
4571     return url;
4572 };

4592 this.parseJSONString = function(jsonString, originURL)
4593 {
4594     if (FBTrace.DBG_JSONVIEWER)
4595         FBTrace.sysout("jsonviewer.parseJSON; " + jsonString);
4596 
4597     // See if this is a Prototype style *-secure request.
4598     var regex = new RegExp(/\s*\/\*-secure-([\s\S]*)\*\/\s*$/);
4599     var matches = regex.exec(jsonString);
4600 
4601     if (matches)
4602     {
4603         jsonString = matches[1];
4604 
4605         if (jsonString[0] == "\\" && jsonString[1] == "n")
4606             jsonString = jsonString.substr(2);
4607 
4608         if (jsonString[jsonString.length-2] == "\\" && jsonString[jsonString.length-1] == "n")
4609             jsonString = jsonString.substr(0, jsonString.length-2);
4610     }
4611 
4612     if (jsonString.indexOf("&&&START&&&"))
4613     {
4614         regex = new RegExp(/&&&START&&& (.+) &&&END&&&/);
4615         matches = regex.exec(jsonString);
4616         if (matches)
4617             jsonString = matches[1];
4618     }
4619 
4620     try
4621     {
4622         var s = Components.utils.Sandbox(originURL);
4623 
4624         // throw on the extra parentheses
4625         return Components.utils.evalInSandbox("(" + jsonString + ")", s);
4626     }
4627     catch(e)
4628     {
4629         if (FBTrace.DBG_JSONVIEWER)
4630             FBTrace.sysout("jsonviewer.parseJSON FAILS on "+originURL+" for \""+jsonString+
4631                 "\" with EXCEPTION "+e, e);
4632     }
4633 
4634     // Let's try to parse it as JSONP.
4635     var reJSONP = /^\s*([A-Za-z0-9_.]+\s*(?:\[.*\]|))\s*\(.*\)/;
4636     var m = reJSONP.exec(jsonString);
4637     if (!m || !m[1])
4638         return null;
4639 
4640     if (FBTrace.DBG_JSONVIEWER)
4641         FBTrace.sysout("jsonviewer.parseJSONP; " + jsonString);
4642 
4643     var callbackName = m[1];
4644 
4645     if (FBTrace.DBG_JSONVIEWER)
4646         FBTrace.sysout("jsonviewer.parseJSONP; Look like we have a JSONP callback: " + callbackName);
4647 
4648     // Replace the original callback (it can be e.g. foo.bar[1]) with simple function name.
4649     jsonString = jsonString.replace(callbackName, "callback");
4650 
4651     try
4652     {
4653         var s = Components.utils.Sandbox(originURL);
4654         s["callback"] = function(object) { return object; };
4655         return Components.utils.evalInSandbox(jsonString, s);
4656     }
4657     catch(ex)
4658     {
4659         if (FBTrace.DBG_JSONVIEWER)
4660             FBTrace.sysout("jsonviewer.parseJSON EXCEPTION", e);
4661     }
4662 
4663     return null;
4664 };

5049

5051         FBTrace.sysout("lib.restoreLocation panel.location: "+panel.location+" restored: "+
5052             restored+" panelState:", panelState);
5053 
5054     return restored;
5055 };
5056 
5057 this.restoreSelection = function(panel, panelState)
5058 {
5059     var needRetry = false;
5060 
5061     if (!panel.selection && panelState && panelState.persistedSelection)
5062     {
5063         var selection = panelState.persistedSelection(panel.context);
5064         if (selection)
5065             panel.select(selection);
5066         else
5067             needRetry = true;
5068     }
5069 
5070     if (!panel.selection)  // Couldn't restore the selection, so select the default object
5071         panel.select(null);
5072 
5073     if (needRetry)
5074     {
5075         function overrideDefaultWithPersistedSelection()
5076         {
5077             if (panel.selection == panel.getDefaultSelection() && panelState.persistedSelection)
5078             {
5079                 var selection = panelState.persistedSelection(panel.context);
5080                 if (selection)
5081                     panel.select(selection);
5082             }
5083 
5084             if (FBTrace.DBG_INITIALIZE)
5085                 FBTrace.sysout("lib.overrideDefaultsWithPersistedValues "+panel.name+
5086                     " panel.location: "+panel.location+" panel.selection: "+panel.selection+
5087                     " panelState:", panelState);
5088         }
5089 
5090         // If we couldn't restore the selection, wait a bit and try again
5091         panel.context.setTimeout(overrideDefaultWithPersistedSelection,
5092             overrideDefaultsWithPersistedValuesTimeout);
5093     }
5094 
5095     if (FBTrace.DBG_INITIALIZE)
5096         FBTrace.sysout("lib.restore "+panel.name+" needRetry "+needRetry+" panel.selection: "+
5097             panel.selection+" panelState:", panelState);
5098 };
5099 
5100 this.restoreObjects = function(panel, panelState)
5101 {
5102     this.restoreLocation(panel, panelState);
5103     this.restoreSelection(panel, panelState);
5104 };
5105 
5106 this.getPersistedState = function(context, panelName)
5107 {
5108     if (!context)
5109         return null;
5110 
5111     var persistedState = context.persistedState;
5112     if (!persistedState)
5113         persistedState = context.persistedState = {};
5114 
5115     if (!persistedState.panelState)
5116         persistedState.panelState = {};
5117 
5118     var panelState = persistedState.panelState[panelName];
5119     if (!panelState)
5120         panelState = persistedState.panelState[panelName] = {};
5121 
5122     return panelState;
5123 };

5174 /**
5175  * @class Searches for text in a given node.
5176  *
5177  * @constructor
5178  * @param {Node} rootNode Node to search
5179  * @param {Function} rowFinder results filter. On find this method will be called
5180  *      with the node containing the matched text as the first parameter. This may
5181  *      be undefined to return the node as is.
5182  */
5183 this.TextSearch = function(rootNode, rowFinder)
5184 {
5185     var doc = rootNode.ownerDocument;
5186     var count, searchRange, startPt;
5187 
5188     /**
5189      * Find the first result in the node.
5190      *
5191      * @param {String} text Text to search for
5192      * @param {boolean} reverse true to perform a reverse search
5193      * @param {boolean} caseSensitive true to perform a case sensitive search
5194      */
5195     this.find = function(text, reverse, caseSensitive)
5196     {
5197         this.text = text;
5198 
5199         finder.findBackwards = !!reverse;
5200         finder.caseSensitive = !!caseSensitive;
5201 
5202         var range = this.range = finder.Find(
5203                 text, searchRange,
5204                 startPt || searchRange,
5205                 searchRange);
5206         var match = range ?  range.startContainer : null;
5207         return this.currentNode = (rowFinder && match ? rowFinder(match) : match);
5208     };
5209 
5210     /**
5211      * Find the next search result
5212      *
5213      * @param {boolean} wrapAround true to wrap the search if the end of range is reached
5214      * @param {boolean} sameNode true to return multiple results from the same text node
5215      * @param {boolean} reverse true to search in reverse
5216      * @param {boolean} caseSensitive true to perform a case sensitive search
5217      */
5218     this.findNext = function(wrapAround, sameNode, reverse, caseSensitive)
5219     {
5220         startPt = undefined;
5221 
5222         if (sameNode && this.range)
5223         {
5224             startPt = this.range.cloneRange();
5225             if (reverse)
5226             {
5227                 startPt.setEnd(startPt.startContainer, startPt.startOffset);
5228             }
5229             else
5230             {
5231                 startPt.setStart(startPt.startContainer, startPt.startOffset+1);
5232             }
5233         }
5234 
5235         if (!startPt)
5236         {
5237             var curNode = this.currentNode ? this.currentNode : rootNode;
5238             startPt = doc.createRange();
5239             try
5240             {
5241                 if (reverse)
5242                 {
5243                     startPt.setStartBefore(curNode);
5244                 }
5245                 else
5246                 {
5247                     startPt.setStartAfter(curNode);
5248                 }
5249             }
5250             catch (e)
5251             {
5252                 if (FBTrace.DBG_ERRORS)
5253                     FBTrace.sysout("lib.TextSearch.findNext setStartAfter fails for nodeType:"+(this.currentNode?this.currentNode.nodeType:rootNode.nodeType),e);
5254                 try {
5255                     FBTrace.sysout("setStart try\n");
5256                     startPt.setStart(curNode);
5257                     FBTrace.sysout("setStart success\n");
5258                 } catch (exc) {
5259                     return;
5260                 }
5261             }
5262         }
5263 
5264         var match = startPt && this.find(this.text, reverse, caseSensitive);
5265         if (!match && wrapAround)
5266         {
5267             this.reset();
5268             return this.find(this.text, reverse, caseSensitive);
5269         }
5270 
5271         return match;
5272     };
5273 
5274     /**
5275      * Resets the instance state to the initial state.
5276      */
5277     this.reset = function()
5278     {
5279         searchRange = doc.createRange();
5280         searchRange.selectNode(rootNode);
5281 
5282         startPt = searchRange;
5283     };
5284 
5285     this.reset();
5286 };

5290 this.SourceBoxTextSearch = function(sourceBox)
5291 {
5292     this.find = function(text, reverse, caseSensitive)
5293     {
5294         this.text = text;
5295 
5296         this.re = new FBL.ReversibleRegExp(text);
5297 
5298         return this.findNext(false, reverse, caseSensitive);
5299     };
5300 
5301     this.findNext = function(wrapAround, reverse, caseSensitive)
5302     {
5303         var lines = sourceBox.lines;
5304         var match = null;
5305         for (var iter = new FBL.ReversibleIterator(lines.length, this.mark, reverse); iter.next();)
5306         {
5307             match = this.re.exec(lines[iter.index], false, caseSensitive);
5308             if (match)
5309             {
5310                 this.mark = iter.index;
5311                 return iter.index;
5312             }
5313         }
5314 
5315         if (!match && wrapAround)
5316         {
5317             this.reset();
5318             return this.findNext(false, reverse, caseSensitive);
5319         }
5320 
5321         return match;
5322     };
5323 
5324     this.reset = function()
5325     {
5326         delete this.mark;
5327     };
5328 
5329     this.reset();
5330 };

5476 this.getDOMMembers = function(object)
5477 {
5478     if (!domMemberCache)
5479     {
5480         domMemberCache = {};
5481 
5482         for (var name in domMemberMap)
5483         {
5484             var builtins = domMemberMap[name];
5485             var cache = domMemberCache[name] = {};
5486 
5487             for (var i = 0; i < builtins.length; ++i)
5488                 cache[builtins[i]] = i;
5489         }
5490     }
5491 
5492     if (object instanceof Window)
5493         { return domMemberCache.Window; }
5494     else if (object instanceof Document || object instanceof XMLDocument)
5495         { return domMemberCache.Document; }
5496     else if (object instanceof Location)
5497         { return domMemberCache.Location; }
5498     else if (object instanceof HTMLImageElement)
5499         { return domMemberCache.HTMLImageElement; }
5500     else if (object instanceof HTMLAnchorElement)
5501         { return domMemberCache.HTMLAnchorElement; }
5502     else if (object instanceof HTMLInputElement)
5503         { return domMemberCache.HTMLInputElement; }
5504     else if (object instanceof HTMLButtonElement)
5505         { return domMemberCache.HTMLButtonElement; }
5506     else if (object instanceof HTMLFormElement)
5507         { return domMemberCache.HTMLFormElement; }
5508     else if (object instanceof HTMLBodyElement)
5509         { return domMemberCache.HTMLBodyElement; }
5510     else if (object instanceof HTMLHtmlElement)
5511         { return domMemberCache.HTMLHtmlElement; }
5512     else if (object instanceof HTMLScriptElement)
5513         { return domMemberCache.HTMLScriptElement; }
5514     else if (object instanceof HTMLTableElement)
5515         { return domMemberCache.HTMLTableElement; }
5516     else if (object instanceof HTMLTableRowElement)
5517         { return domMemberCache.HTMLTableRowElement; }
5518     else if (object instanceof HTMLTableCellElement)
5519         { return domMemberCache.HTMLTableCellElement; }
5520     else if (object instanceof HTMLIFrameElement)
5521         { return domMemberCache.HTMLIFrameElement; }
5522     else if (object instanceof SVGSVGElement)
5523         { return domMemberCache.SVGSVGElement; }
5524     else if (object instanceof SVGElement)
5525         { return domMemberCache.SVGElement; }
5526     else if (object instanceof Element)
5527         { return domMemberCache.Element; }
5528     else if (object instanceof Text || object instanceof CDATASection)
5529         { return domMemberCache.Text; }
5530     else if (object instanceof Attr)
5531         { return domMemberCache.Attr; }
5532     else if (object instanceof Node)
5533         { return domMemberCache.Node; }
5534     else if (object instanceof Event || object instanceof EventCopy)
5535         { return domMemberCache.Event; }
5536 
5537     return null;
5538 };

6336 this.isDOMConstant = function(object, name)
6337 {
6338     if (name == undefined)
6339     {
6340         return isDOMConstantDep({},object);
6341     }
6342 
6343     // The constant map has also its own prototype, but it isn't considered to be a constant.
6344     if (name == "__proto__")
6345         return false;
6346 
6347     if (!(object instanceof Window ||
6348         object instanceof Node ||
6349         object instanceof Location ||
6350         object instanceof Event ||
6351         object instanceof EventCopy))
6352         return false;
6353 
6354     return domConstantMap.hasOwnProperty(name);
6355 }

7862 this.formatNumber = function(number)
7863 {
7864     number += "";
7865     var x = number.split(".");
7866     var x1 = x[0];
7867     var x2 = x.length > 1 ? "." + x[1] : "";
7868     var rgx = /(\d+)(\d{3})/;
7869     while (rgx.test(x1))
7870         x1 = x1.replace(rgx, "$1" + "," + "$2");
7871     return x1 + x2;
7872 }

7874 // ************************************************************************************************
7875 // File Size Utils
7876 
7877 this.formatSize = function(bytes)
7878 {
7879     // xxxHonza, XXXjjb: Why Firebug.sizePrecision is not set in Chromebug?
7880     if (typeof(Firebug.sizePrecision) == "undefined")
7881         Firebug.sizePrecision = 2;
7882 
7883     // Get size precision (number of decimal places from the preferences)
7884     // and make sure it's within limits.
7885     var sizePrecision = Firebug.sizePrecision;
7886     sizePrecision = (sizePrecision > 2) ? 2 : sizePrecision;
7887     sizePrecision = (sizePrecision < -1) ? -1 : sizePrecision;
7888 
7889     if (sizePrecision == -1)
7890         return bytes + " B";
7891 
7892     var a = Math.pow(10, sizePrecision);
7893 
7894     if (bytes == -1 || bytes == undefined)
7895         return "?";
7896     else if (bytes == 0)
7897         return "0";
7898     else if (bytes < 1024)
7899         return bytes + " B";
7900     else if (bytes < (1024*1024))
7901         return Math.round((bytes/1024)*a)/a + " KB";
7902     else
7903         return Math.round((bytes/(1024*1024))*a)/a + " MB";
7904 }

7909 this.formatTime = function(elapsed)
7910 {
7911     if (elapsed == -1)
7912         return "";
7913     else if (elapsed == 0)
7914         return "0";
7915     else if (elapsed < 1000)
7916         return elapsed + "ms";
7917     else if (elapsed < 60000)
7918         return (Math.round(elapsed/10) / 100) + "s";
7919     else
7920     {
7921         var min = Math.floor(elapsed/60000);
7922         var sec = (elapsed % 60000);
7923         return min + "m " + (Math.round((elapsed/1000)%60)) + "s";
7924     }

7929 this.ReversibleIterator = function(length, start, reverse)
7930 {
7931     this.length = length;
7932     this.index = start;
7933     this.reversed = !!reverse;
7934 
7935     this.next = function() {
7936         if (this.index === undefined || this.index === null) {
7937             this.index = this.reversed ? length : -1;
7938         }
7939         this.index += this.reversed ? -1 : 1;
7940 
7941         return 0 <= this.index && this.index < length;
7942     };
7943     this.reverse = function() {
7944         this.reversed = !this.reversed;
7945     };
7946 };

7948 /**
7949  * @class Implements a RegExp-like object that will search for the literal value
7950  * of a given string, rather than the regular expression. This allows for
7951  * iterative literal searches without having to escape user input strings
7952  * to prevent invalid regular expressions from being used.
7953  *
7954  * @constructor
7955  * @param {String} literal Text to search for
7956  * @param {Boolean} reverse Truthy to preform a reverse search, falsy to perform a forward seach
7957  * @param {Boolean} caseSensitive Truthy to perform a case sensitive search, falsy to perform a case insensitive search.
7958  */
7959 this.LiteralRegExp = function(literal, reverse, caseSensitive)
7960 {
7961     var searchToken = (!caseSensitive) ? literal.toLowerCase() : literal;
7962 
7963     this.__defineGetter__("global", function() { return true; });
7964     this.__defineGetter__("multiline", function() { return true; });
7965     this.__defineGetter__("reverse", function() { return reverse; });
7966     this.__defineGetter__("ignoreCase", function() { return !caseSensitive; });
7967     this.lastIndex = 0;
7968 
7969     this.exec = function(text)
7970     {
7971         if (!text)
7972             return null;
7973 
7974         var searchText = (!caseSensitive) ? text.toLowerCase() : text,
7975             startIndex = (reverse ? text.length-1 : 0) + this.lastIndex,
7976             index;
7977 
7978         if (0 <= startIndex && startIndex < text.length)
7979             index = searchText[reverse ? "lastIndexOf" : "indexOf"](searchToken, startIndex);
7980         else
7981             index = -1;
7982 
7983         if (index >= 0)
7984         {
7985             var ret = [ text.substr(index, searchToken.length) ];
7986             ret.index = index;
7987             ret.input = text;
7988             this.lastIndex = index + (reverse ? -1*text.length : searchToken.length);
7989             return ret;
7990         }
7991         else
7992             this.lastIndex = 0;
7993 
7994         return null;
7995     };
7996     this.test = function(text)
7997     {
7998         if (!text)
7999             return false;
8000 
8001         var searchText = (!caseSensitive) ? text.toLowerCase() : text;
8002         return searchText.indexOf(searchToken) >= 0;
8003     };
8004 };
8005 
8006 this.ReversibleRegExp = function(regex, flags)
8007 {
8008     var re = {};
8009 
8010     function expression(text, reverse) {
8011         return text + (reverse ? "(?![\\s\\S]*" + text + ")" : "");
8012     }
8013     function flag(flags, caseSensitive) {
8014         return (flags || "") + (caseSensitive ? "" : "i");
8015     }
8016 
8017     this.exec = function(text, reverse, caseSensitive, lastMatch)
8018     {
8019         // Ensure we have a regex
8020         var key = (reverse ? "r" : "n") + (caseSensitive ? "n" : "i");
8021         if (!re[key])
8022         {
8023             try
8024             {
8025                 if (Firebug.searchUseRegularExpression)
8026                     re[key] = new RegExp(expression(regex, reverse), flag(flags, caseSensitive));
8027                 else
8028                     re[key] = new FBL.LiteralRegExp(regex, reverse, caseSensitive);
8029             }
8030             catch (ex)
8031             {
8032                 // The user likely entered an invalid regular expression or is in the
8033                 // process of entering a valid one. Treat this as a plain text search
8034                 re[key] = new FBL.LiteralRegExp(regex, reverse, caseSensitive);
8035             }
8036         }
8037 
8038         // Modify as needed to all for iterative searches
8039         var indexOffset = 0;
8040         var searchText = text;
8041         if (lastMatch) {
8042             if (reverse) {
8043                 searchText = text.substr(0, lastMatch.index);
8044             } else {
8045                 indexOffset = lastMatch.index+lastMatch[0].length;
8046                 searchText = text.substr(indexOffset);
8047             }
8048         }
8049 
8050         var curRe = re[key];
8051         curRe.lastIndex = 0;
8052         var ret = curRe.exec(searchText);
8053         if (ret) {
8054             ret.input = text;
8055             ret.index = ret.index + indexOffset;
8056             ret.reverse = reverse;
8057             ret.caseSensitive = caseSensitive;
8058         }
8059         return ret;
8060     };
8061 };

8070         return object;

8073     // instance of StorageObsolete)

8075         return object;
8076

8078         return object.wrappedJSObject;
8079 
8080     return object;

8128 /**
8129  * Compare expected Firebug version with the current Firebug installed.
8130  * @param {Object} expectedVersion Expected version of Firebug.
8131  * @returns
8132  * -1 the current version is smaller
8133  *  0 the current version is the same
8134  *  1 the current version is bigger
8135  *
8136  * @example:
8137  * if (compareFirebugVersion("1.6") >= 0)
8138  * {
8139  *     // The current version is Firebug 1.6+
8140  * }
8141  */
8142 this.checkFirebugVersion = function(expectedVersion)
8143 {
8144     if (!expectedVersion)
8145         return 1;
8146 
8147     var version = Firebug.getVersion();
8148 
8149     // Adapt to Firefox version scheme.
8150     expectedVersion = expectedVersion.replace('X', '', "g");
8151     version = version.replace('X', '', "g");
8152 
8153     // Use Firefox comparator service.
8154     return versionChecker.compare(version, expectedVersion);
8155 }
